trigger.sequence:
1. Create a constructor function that allocates a small plain object (obj_inner) with known shape
2. Store obj_inner into a property of another pre-existing tenured object (obj_outer.prop = obj_inner) — this generates a PostWriteBarrier with obj_inner as value (operand 1)
3. The escape analysis sees obj_inner used only as PostWriteBarrier value operand and in StoreFixedSlot as container — incorrectly considers it non-escaped
4. obj_inner gets scalar-replaced (eliminated from heap)
5. Access obj_outer.prop — the slot contains a dangling/invalid reference since obj_inner was never actually allocated
6. Use obj_outer.prop.someField — type confusion / use-after-free

